# Global git ignore, managed by dotfiles. The installer symlinks this directory
# to ~/.config/git, so this file becomes ~/.config/git/ignore — the path git uses
# for global excludes when core.excludesFile is unset — and applies to every
# repository on the machine. Project-specific ignores belong in each repository's
# own .gitignore.

